Fix undefined MBED_CONF_QSPI_NUM_STATUS_REGISTER in QSPIFBlockDevice.

The pinned mbed-os master (d723bf9) references MBED_CONF_QSPI_NUM_STATUS_REGISTER
in QSPIFBlockDevice::_handle_vendor_quirks() (Macronix case), but the qspif
mbed_lib.json defines the parameter under the "qspif" library, so the generated
macro is MBED_CONF_QSPIF_QSPI_NUM_STATUS_REGISTER. This makes the H7 build fail
with "'MBED_CONF_QSPI_NUM_STATUS_REGISTER' was not declared in this scope".

Arduino core patch 0190 (QSPI Adesto quirks) would normally reconcile this file,
but it does not apply against this newer mbed-os. Correct the reference to the
macro that is actually defined.

diff --git a/storage/blockdevice/COMPONENT_QSPIF/source/QSPIFBlockDevice.cpp b/storage/blockdevice/COMPONENT_QSPIF/source/QSPIFBlockDevice.cpp
--- a/storage/blockdevice/COMPONENT_QSPIF/source/QSPIFBlockDevice.cpp
+++ b/storage/blockdevice/COMPONENT_QSPIF/source/QSPIFBlockDevice.cpp
@@ -1093,7 +1093,7 @@ int QSPIFBlockDevice::_handle_vendor_quirks()
             tr_debug("Applying quirks for macronix");
             _needs_fast_mode = true;
-            _num_status_registers = MBED_CONF_QSPI_NUM_STATUS_REGISTER;
+            _num_status_registers = MBED_CONF_QSPIF_QSPI_NUM_STATUS_REGISTER;
             _read_status_reg_2_inst = QSPIF_INST_RDCR;
             _attempt_4_byte_addressing = false;
             break;
